## Risk Configuration

### Risk Appetite Statement
  [Write your organisation's risk appetite in plain language]
  Example: "We have a low appetite for regulatory and compliance risk
  (zero tolerance for regulatory breach). We have a medium appetite for
  operational disruption (can tolerate up to [N] hours before escalation).
  We have a medium appetite for financial risk (can absorb up to [X] from
  a single operational failure without board notification)."

### Risk Appetite Thresholds (Residual Score)
  Acceptable (no action):     1-4 -- ACCEPT
  Monitor (quarterly review): 5-9 -- ACCEPT with monitoring
  Mitigate (action required): 10-16 -- MITIGATE within [timeframe]
  Escalate (COO-level):       17-20 -- ESCALATE within [timeframe]
  Critical (Board-level):     21-25 -- IMMEDIATE escalation

### Risk Scoring (5x5 Matrix)
  LIKELIHOOD:
    1 -- Rare:           <5% probability in next 12 months
    2 -- Unlikely:       5-20% probability
    3 -- Possible:       20-50% probability
    4 -- Likely:         50-80% probability
    5 -- Almost certain: >80% probability

  IMPACT:
    1 -- Negligible:  <5K cost; <1hr disruption; no regulatory consequence
    2 -- Minor:       5K-50K; 1-4hr disruption; minor regulatory note
    3 -- Moderate:    50K-250K; 4-24hr disruption; regulatory inquiry
    4 -- Significant: 250K-1M; 1-7 day disruption; regulatory action
    5 -- Critical:    >1M; >7 days disruption; licence/enforcement action

  RISK SCORE = Likelihood x Impact
    LOW:      1-4
    MEDIUM:   5-9
    HIGH:     10-16
    CRITICAL: 17-25

### Risk Register
  Location:       [Document store URL]
  Review cadence: Quarterly for HIGH/CRITICAL; bi-annual for MEDIUM; annual for LOW
  Risk owner:     [Primary: COO | Risk committee if applicable]

### Escalation Contacts
